<paragraph xmlns:gate="http://www.gate.ac.uk" gate:gateId="0" gate:annotMaxId="303">Agostini, Pietro Simone, Italian composer; <Event_Birth gate:gateId="302" RE="1650" Pred="birth" Pred-tyoe="time"><Birth gate:gateId="300" predict="birth">b.</Birth> <Location gate:gateId="235" rule1="Location1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Rome</Location>, c. <Date gate:gateId="236" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1650</Date></Event_Birth>. He was in the service of the Duke of Parma as maestro di cappella. He wrote 6 operas: Tolemeo (<Location gate:gateId="238" locType="city" rule1="Location1" gate:matches="238;245;247" rule2="LocFinal">Venice</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="239" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1668</Date>) ; Ippolita (<Location gate:gateId="240" rule1="Location1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Milan</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="241" rule1="TempYear3" gate:matches="241;243" rule2="YearOnlyFinal" kind="date">1670</Date>) ; La costanza di Rosmonda (<Location gate:gateId="242" rule1="Location1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Genoa</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="243" rule1="TempYear3" gate:matches="241;243" rule2="YearOnlyFinal" kind="date">1670</Date>) ; Adelinda (Aricia, <Date gate:gateId="244" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1673</Date>); 7/ Ratto delle Sabine (<Location gate:gateId="245" locType="city" rule1="Location1" gate:matches="238;245;247" rule2="LocFinal">Venice</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="246" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1680</Date>); and Floridea (<Location gate:gateId="247" locType="city" rule1="Location1" gate:matches="238;245;247" rule2="LocFinal">Venice</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="248" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1687</Date>). Some of his operas were written in collaboration with Busca, Ziani and others. He also wrote oratorios, motets and secular cantatas. </paragraph>